cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SY, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with computational topology and algorithms for computing persistence and homology generators of simplicial complexes embedded in $\mathbb{R}^3$. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also uses efficient data structures and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper involves combinatorial and algebraic methods, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses some results from control theory, which could suggest cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves numerical computations, which could suggest cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
